'''Damián Josué Bobadilla Benítez''' (born 11 July 2001) is a Paraguayan professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[São Paulo FC|São Paulo]] and the  [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

==Club career==

=== Cerro Porteño ===
Trained in the youth sectors of [[Cerro Porteño]], he made his professional debut on 5 May 2021, against [[Atlético Mineiro]] in the [[2021 Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2021/05/17/damian-bobadilla-la-capitania-en-cerro-el-legado-de-su-padre-y-sus-referentes/|title=Versus / Damián Bobadilla; la capitanía en Cerro, el legado de su padre y sus referentes|access-date=7 October 2023|last=Martínez|first=Carlos|date=17 May 2021|website=Versus|language=es |archive-date=7 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231007025634/https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2021/05/17/damian-bobadilla-la-capitania-en-cerro-el-legado-de-su-padre-y-sus-referentes/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hoy.com.py/deportes/damian-bobadilla-sobre-canteranos-de-cerro-lo-unico-que-queremos-es-jugar|title=Diario HOY {{!}} Damián Bobadilla, sobre canteranos de Cerro: "Lo único que queremos es jugar"|access-date=7 October 2023|last=Candia|first=Pedro|date=25 April 2022|website=Diario HOY|language=es |archive-date=25 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425173451/https://www.hoy.com.py/deportes/damian-bobadilla-sobre-canteranos-de-cerro-lo-unico-que-queremos-es-jugar |url-status=live }}</ref>

Bobadilla was elected with the “Futbolista de la Gente” award for the [[2023 Paraguayan Primera División season|2023 edition]] of the Paraguayan Championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ip.gov.py/ip/premiaron-a-los-mejores-del-futbol-paraguayo-en-el-2023/ |title=Premiaron a los mejores del fútbol paraguayo en el 2023 |website=Agencia de Informacíon Paraguaya |date=5 December 2023 |language=es |archive-date=26 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250126192635/https://www.ip.gov.py/ip/2023/12/05/premiaron-a-los-mejores-del-futbol-paraguayo-en-el-2023/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== São Paulo ===
On 20 December 2023, Bobadilla moved to Brazil, signing a four-year contract with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] club [[São Paulo FC|São Paulo]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 December 2023 |title=Tricolor acerta a contratação de Damián Bobadilla |trans-title=Tricolor agrees to sign Damián Bobadilla |url=http://www.saopaulofc.net/noticias/noticias/spfc-/2023/12/20/tricolor-acerta-a-contratacao-de-damian-bobadilla |access-date=20 December 2023 |publisher=São Paulo FC |language=pt-br |archive-date=3 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240303222323/https://www.saopaulofc.net/tricolor-acerta-a-contratacao-de-damian-bobadilla/ |url-status=live }}</ref> for a reported fee of around $3 million for 60% of the player's economic rights.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 December 2023 |title=São Paulo anuncia a contratação de Damián Bobadilla |trans-title=São Paulo announces signing of Damián Bobadilla |url=https://tntsports.com.br/futebolbrasileiro/Sao-Paulo-anuncia-a-contratacao-de-Damian-Bobadilla-20231220-0008.html |access-date=20 December 2023 |website=TNT Sports |language=pt-br |archive-date=20 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231220183529/https://tntsports.com.br/futebolbrasileiro/Sao-Paulo-anuncia-a-contratacao-de-Damian-Bobadilla-20231220-0008.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

==International career==
Bobadilla made his debut for the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]] on 11 June 2024 in a friendly against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] at [[Estadio Nacional Julio Martínez Prádanos]]. He substituted [[Andrés Cubas]] at half-time as Chile won 3–0.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/701636/|title=Chile v Paraguay game report|date=11 June 2024 |archive-date=12 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240612024619/https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/701636/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Bobadilla played the [[2024 Copa América]], missing [[São Paulo FC]] seven [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|league]] matches in the process. In order to not be absent in more games with his club, he opted to decline the [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|Paraguay]] call up for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazetaesportiva.com/times/sao-paulo/bobadilla-abdica-das-olimpiadas-para-ajudar-o-sao-paulo-e-ganha-elogios-de-zubeldia-foi-premiado/|title=Bobadilla abdica das Olimpíadas para ajudar o São Paulo e ganha elogios de Zubeldía: "Foi premiado" |website=Gazeta Esportiva |date=23 August 2024 |language=pt |archive-date=7 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240907034944/https://www.gazetaesportiva.com/times/sao-paulo/bobadilla-abdica-das-olimpiadas-para-ajudar-o-sao-paulo-e-ganha-elogios-de-zubeldia-foi-premiado/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==

Damián is son of the former goalkeeper [[Aldo Bobadilla]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Rojas |first=Arturo |date=25 October 2019 |title=Versus / Bobadilla, sobre su hijo que está en Cerro: "Él remó desde abajo" |url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2019/10/25/bobadilla-sobre-su-hijo-que-esta-en-cerro-el-remo-desde-abajo/ |access-date=7 October 2023 |website=Versus |language=es |archive-date=7 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231007025635/https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2019/10/25/bobadilla-sobre-su-hijo-que-esta-en-cerro-el-remo-desde-abajo/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

